<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="598" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,255,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,290,314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface dark brown except for yellow lateral margins of pronotum, yellow humeri and yellow mediolateral patches on the elytra; elytral coloration very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nascimento et Bocakova, 2010" authorityName="Nascimento et Bocakova" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Brasilycus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1265,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Brasilycus bolivianus</emphasis>
Nascimento 
<emphasis box="[1417,1436,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">et</emphasis>
Bocakova, 
<number box="[274,330,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</taxonomicName>
, which has a transverse median yellow band; phallus of 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1090,360,383]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Brasilycus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[958,1090,360,383]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">B. peruanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1099,1185,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in distal third as thick (measured dorsoventrally) as paramerae in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="598" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,255,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,428,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Description.</emphasis>
Whole body and dorsal surface dark brown, except for yellow lateral margins of pronotum, humeral and mediolateral spots of elytra, trochanters, bases of femora, and antennomere 
<number box="[997,1023,464,487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="11.0">11</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1043,1105,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,852,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,818,1908]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brasilycus peruanus sp. nov. (1) Habitus; (2) Head and pronotum; (3) Basal antennomeres; (4 – 6) male genitalia in ventral, lateral, and dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm (Fig. 1), scale = 0.5 mm (Figs 2 – 6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221892/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
Fig. 
<number box="[1092,1105,464,487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eyes medium-sized, distance between eyes 
<number box="[300,333,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.3">1.3</number>
x longer than maximal eye diameter. Maxillary palpi dark brown, only palpomere 
<number box="[1205,1218,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
yellow. Labial palpi brown. Terminal palpomeres of both palpi apically pointed. Antennae serrate, reaching elytral 
<number box="[1150,1164,533,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1174,1186,533,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="3.0">3</number>
, antennomere 
<number box="[1341,1354,533,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as 
<number box="[181,194,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[210,276,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,852,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,818,1908]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brasilycus peruanus sp. nov. (1) Habitus; (2) Head and pronotum; (3) Basal antennomeres; (4 – 6) male genitalia in ventral, lateral, and dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm (Fig. 1), scale = 0.5 mm (Figs 2 – 6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221892/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
Fig. 
<number box="[261,276,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[419,485,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,852,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,818,1908]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brasilycus peruanus sp. nov. (1) Habitus; (2) Head and pronotum; (3) Basal antennomeres; (4 – 6) male genitalia in ventral, lateral, and dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm (Fig. 1), scale = 0.5 mm (Figs 2 – 6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221892/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
Fig. 
<number box="[471,485,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[501,534,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x wider than long, provided with median longitudinal carina forming minute areola basally, posterior angles of pronotum projected obliquely backwards. Elytra elongate, 
<number box="[1087,1121,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="3.2">3.2</number>
x longer than humeral width. Each elytron with 
<number box="[348,361,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="3.0">3</number>
longitudinal costae, costa 
<number box="[646,659,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
absent in distal quarter. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1181,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,852,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,818,1908]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brasilycus peruanus sp. nov. (1) Habitus; (2) Head and pronotum; (3) Basal antennomeres; (4 – 6) male genitalia in ventral, lateral, and dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm (Fig. 1), scale = 0.5 mm (Figs 2 – 6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221892/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
Figs 
<number box="[1144,1181,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4-6</number>
</figureCitation>
) with paramerae longer than half length of phallus, tapered distally, phallus broad dorsoventrally in distal third. Body length: 
<quantity box="[1251,1336,672,695]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
, humeral width: 
<quantity box="[226,311,706,729]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,829,740,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,255,764]" box="[199,829,740,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,740,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Remark.</emphasis>
Left antennomeres 
<number box="[511,564,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="9.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="7.0">7–11</number>
of the 
<typeStatus box="[638,731,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">holotype</typeStatus>
missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
